Can't we use one parameter to assess the investment project?

13:49.200 --> 13:51.200
Why use a lot?

13:51.200 --> 13:54.200
There are such situations, there are such questions

13:54.200 --> 13:56.200
What is better?

13:56.200 --> 14:00.200
The absolute value of NPV or the relative value of IRR?

14:02.200 --> 14:06.200
The question is controversial, there is no definite answer

14:06.200 --> 14:08.200
But here we need to clarify

14:08.200 --> 14:12.200
That IRR, unlike NPV, is a capricious lady

14:12.200 --> 14:14.200
And has its nuances

14:14.200 --> 14:17.200
Before we talk about these nuances

14:17.200 --> 14:21.200
It should be clarified that there are different types of money flows

14:21.200 --> 14:25.200
And depending on the type, there can be nuances related to IRR

14:25.200 --> 14:29.200
There are three main types of money flows

14:29.200 --> 14:32.200
Traditional money flow

14:32.200 --> 14:35.200
This is, look at the next slide

14:35.200 --> 14:38.200
Traditional money flow, borrowed money flow

14:38.200 --> 14:44.200
And several types of non-traditional money flows

14:44.200 --> 14:46.200
Let's start with the traditional

14:46.200 --> 14:48.200
Traditional money flow

14:48.200 --> 14:51.200
It means that you spent money at first

14:51.200 --> 14:53.200
That is, you have a flow at first

14:53.200 --> 14:56.200
And then every period you have a flow of money

14:56.200 --> 15:01.200
Borrowed type of money flows

15:01.200 --> 15:04.200
It assumes that you have attracted resources from somewhere

15:04.200 --> 15:09.200
And then you spend them gradually every period

15:09.200 --> 15:14.200
Finally, non-traditional is a combination of the first two

15:14.200 --> 15:17.200
But in a situation where over time

15:17.200 --> 15:20.200
Your money flows change signs

15:20.200 --> 15:25.200
That is, today you invested money, it is a flow

15:25.200 --> 15:28.200
Then you had inflows for three years in a row

15:28.200 --> 15:33.200
And then, for example, in 2004 you had some problems

15:33.200 --> 15:35.200
You have a flow of money resources

15:35.200 --> 15:37.200
And then again an inflow

15:37.200 --> 15:39.200
It will be a non-traditional money flow

15:39.200 --> 15:45.200
And it leads to the fact that you have not one IRR, but two

15:45.200 --> 15:47.200
Oddly enough

15:47.200 --> 15:50.200
So, what do money flows look like?

15:50.200 --> 15:55.200
The next slide shows us what a traditional money flow looks like

15:55.200 --> 16:00.200
Pay attention, with the growth of profitability, the NPV is reduced

16:00.200 --> 16:02.200
This is quite natural

16:02.200 --> 16:05.200
With the growth of profitability, the NPV is reduced

16:05.200 --> 16:16.200
And IRR, you see, is the point where the line of our project intersects with the horizontal axis

16:16.200 --> 16:20.200
The money flow of the borrowed type is the reverse line

16:20.200 --> 16:23.200
By the way, the lines may not necessarily be curved

16:23.200 --> 16:25.200
The project line can be straight

16:25.200 --> 16:27.200
So it's just a drawing

16:27.200 --> 16:33.200
NPV, in this picture you see, grows with the growth of profitability

16:33.200 --> 16:36.200
This is a money flow of the borrowed type

16:36.200 --> 16:39.200
Finally, a non-traditional money flow

16:39.200 --> 16:41.200
One of its varieties

16:41.200 --> 16:44.200
In this case, it is a borrowed money flow

16:44.200 --> 16:49.200
You see that with the growth of profitability, the NPV grows

16:49.200 --> 16:53.200
Then comes the moment, the point of X-interruption

16:53.200 --> 17:01.200
After which, with the growth of profitability, the NPV begins to fall

17:02.200 --> 17:06.200
In this case, we will have two IRR in the project

17:09.200 --> 17:18.200
In principle, the maximum number of IRR is the number of times that the money flows change the sign from positive to negative or vice versa

17:18.200 --> 17:26.200
It is obvious that with the multiplicity of IRR in the project, its use is not purposeful

17:26.200 --> 17:28.200
There is nothing to talk about

17:28.200 --> 17:32.200
But if for some reason you want to have this parameter

17:32.200 --> 17:38.200
You can do the calculation and get rid of negative money flows

17:38.200 --> 17:45.200
And thus bring your project to the traditional or borrowed type

17:45.200 --> 17:47.200
How can this be done?

17:47.200 --> 17:52.200
Let's look at the next two slides

17:52.200 --> 17:56.200
So, this will be an example of a calculation

17:56.200 --> 18:04.200
We have a project in which we spend 100 units in the first year

18:04.200 --> 18:09.200
Then in the second year we get 60 units of income

18:09.200 --> 18:12.200
Then we get 70 units of income

18:12.200 --> 18:19.200
